@Ιασων I see that you've read the comments, and no doubt you already know that the "will call" window (or desk, or whatever} is where you pick up tickets you've paid for in advance. 

But it also applies to other circumstances. Warehouses often have a "will call" desk where people can pick up merchandise. Typically they've already paid via the company's website, but sometimes they use an established line of credit. It's useful if the customer lives relatively near the website; it's a way to get what they need quickly, without having to wait for it to be shipped or delivered via a company truck. 

I've worked at several warehouse will-calls, because I always tended to volunteer for the stuff nobody else wants to do. It takes patience. Often the customer is already stressed out and in a hurry, so working that job often involves getting yelled at for things you have no control over. It also requires a comprehensive knowledge of most of what the watehouse sells, and the ability to solve problems on the fly.

